  "text": "As an extracellular matrix protein, collagen VI is uniquely positioned to have a profound effect on both the muscle fiber and the surrounding connective tissue ( Fig. 1 ). Direct effects on the muscle have been reproduced in targeted gene disruption of COL6A1 in the mouse, exhibiting muscle fiber necrosis with regeneration and variation in muscle fiber size, and reduced contractile force [CITATION_1] .",
